<h1>Basics</h1>

<p>A plot is a combination of data, mappings, geometric objects (geoms), scales and theme.</p>

<dl class="row ml-auto mr-auto">

    <dt class="col-sm-2">Data</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-10">A source can operate directly on your business objects. Optionally handles how your plots refresh on data updates.</dd>

    <dt class="col-sm-2">Mappings</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-10">Specify how variables relate to visual properties with lambda expressions.</dd>

    <dt class="col-sm-2">Geoms</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-10">Instruct the choice of graphical objects that best describe your data.</dd>

    <dt class="col-sm-2">Scales</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-10">Control how variables get translated to positional and aesthetic visual properties.</dd>

    <dt class="col-sm-2">Theme</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-10">Controls how elements are styled allowing seamless integration with your designs and brand.</dd>

</dl>

